.SH NAME
TextMetrics.width \- TextMetrics: width property
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The read\-only \f[B]\f[CB]width\f[B]\f[R] property of the
\f[CR]TextMetrics\f[R] interface contains the text\[cq]s advance width
(the width of that inline box) in CSS pixels.
.SH EXAMPLES
Start with this \f[CR]<canvas>\f[R] element:
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]canvas\f[R] id=\[dq]canvas\[dq]></\f[B]canvas\f[R]>
.EE
.PP
You can get a \f[CR]TextMetrics\f[R] object using the following code:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] ctx = canvas.getContext(\[dq]2d\[dq]);

\f[B]let\f[R] text = ctx.measureText(\[dq]foo\[dq]); \f[I]// TextMetrics object\f[R]
text.width; \f[I]// 16;\f[R]
.EE
